  <section class="home-section home-intro">
    <p class="home-lede">I help people and organizations make sense of evidence, context, and competing priorities &ndash; bringing clearer thinking, stronger grounding, and practical direction to complex work.</p>
    <p>I&rsquo;ve spent 10+ years in and around global health ethics, after formative detours through humanitarian relief, hospitality, and ecology.</p>
    <p>I&rsquo;m interested in tools, broadly: things you hold in your hand (hand tools, cameras, computers), and things you hold in your head (concepts, frameworks, protocols). I&rsquo;m especially interested in tools that sharpen judgment and intuition without replacing them.</p>
